Pattern	Meaning	Output
\d	One digit	['3', '5', '1', '2']
\d+	One or more consecutive digits	['3', '5', '12']
Function	Purpose
re.search()	Finds the first match anywhere in the string.
re.match()	Checks for a match only at the beginning of the string.
re.findall()	Returns all matches as a list.
re.finditer()	Returns an iterator over all matches.
re.sub()	Replaces matching text.
re.split()	Splits a string using a regex pattern.